# Project
Read docs/PRODUCT.md for product context and docs/ARCHITECTURE.md for system design.
At the start of any session, read docs/PROGRESS.md to understand current state.
Feature work is driven by specs in docs/features/. Implement one task at a time.
Task checkboxes live only in docs/features/ specs; ARCHITECTURE.md contains no
task lists.

# Stack (do not substitute or add alternatives)
- Next.js 15 (App Router) + React 19 + TypeScript (strict)
- Tailwind CSS v4 + shadcn/ui (components/ui)
- Drizzle ORM + PostgreSQL (Neon)
- Better Auth (auth) · Stripe (billing) · Resend + react-email (email)
- Vitest (unit) · Playwright (e2e) · Biome (lint/format)

# Hard conventions
- Server Components by default. Add "use client" only when interactivity requires it.
- FEATURE-MODULE structure: all code for a feature lives in src/modules/<feature>/
  (components/, actions.ts, service.ts, queries.ts, schemas.ts). See
  src/modules/_example/README.md. Pages in src/app are thin composers.
- Modules never import another module's internals — only its service.ts.
  UI components never import from src/db directly; only service.ts/queries.ts do.
- Shared homes (do not invent new locations): primitives → src/components/ui ·
  hooks → src/hooks · types → src/types · emails → src/emails (or module-owned) ·
  cross-cutting server utils → src/server · test factories → tests/factories.ts ·
  one-off scripts → scripts/
- Validate ALL external input with Zod at the boundary. Infer TS types from schemas.
- Services throw typed errors. Actions catch and return { data } | { error }
  discriminated unions. Never throw raw errors to the client.
- Reuse components/ui primitives before creating new components. Extend via cva
  variants — never restyle shadcn primitives with one-off inline classes.
- Brand values (names, URLs, colors, plans) come ONLY from config/brand.ts and CSS
  tokens in app/globals.css. Never hardcode brand-specific values in components.
- Money is integer cents. Timestamps are UTC in the DB, formatted at the edge.
- Multi-tenancy: every tenant-owned table has org_id. Every query is scoped by
  org_id via the withOrg() helper in db/. Never write an unscoped tenant query.

# Behavior contract
- Before implementing, state a 3–6 line plan. If the task is ambiguous, ask ONE
  clarifying question instead of guessing.
- Touch only files needed for the current task. Do not refactor, rename, or
  "improve" code outside scope.
- Do not add dependencies without asking. Do not re-litigate decisions recorded
  in docs/DECISIONS.md.
- After completing a task: run typecheck and affected tests; tick the task
  checkbox in the feature spec; update docs/PROGRESS.md (current state, known
  issues, next up).
- If you find an out-of-scope bug, record it in PROGRESS.md "Known issues" —
  do not fix it now.
